MFQ Test Plan for E-commerce System
├─ M Models
│  ├─ 1. End-to-End Order Business Flow Model
│  │  ├─ Normal Flow: Browse Products → Add to Cart → Place Order → Payment → Inventory Deduction → WMS Shipment → Sign-off → Order Completion
│  │  └─ Exception Branches: Payment Failure / Order Cancellation / Partial Shipment / Return & Refund / Overselling
│  ├─ 2. Order State Machine Model
│  │  ├─ Order Status: Pending Payment, Paid, Pending Shipment, Shipped, Signed Off, Completed, Closed, Refunded
│  │  ├─ Valid State Transition Rules
│  │  ├─ Interception & Validation for Invalid State Jumps
│  │  └─ Automatic Transition on Timeout (Auto-close orders with expired pending payment)
│  ├─ 3. Inventory State Model
│  │  ├─ Inventory Status: Available, Pre-locked, Deducted, Released, Restored after Return
│  │  ├─ Order Placement: Pre-lock product inventory
│  │  ├─ Payment Success: Convert pre-locked inventory to formal deduction
│  │  ├─ Order Cancellation / Payment Timeout: Release pre-locked inventory
│  │  └─ Return / Rejection: Restore inventory to available status
│  ├─ 4. External System Interaction Model
│  │  ├─ Storefront ↔ WMS: Outbound Order, Shipment Notification, Sign-off Notification
│  │  ├─ Storefront ↔ SC2P Payment System: Payment Callback, Refund Callback
│  │  ├─ Synchronization Modes: Synchronous Call, Asynchronous Message, Callback Notification
│  │  └─ Basic Mechanisms: Request Retry, Message Idempotency, Exception Fallback
│  └─ 5. Data Consistency Boundary Model
│     ├─ Strong Consistency Scope: Real-time inventory deduction, order payment status
│     ├─ Eventual Consistency Scope: WMS shipment status, cross-system inventory reconciliation
│     └─ Reconciliation Nodes: T+1 Inventory Reconciliation, Order Status Reconciliation, Message Log Reconciliation
├─ F Functional
│  ├─ 1. Core Main Flow (Normal Path)
│  │  ├─ Full Process: Place Order → Payment → Shipment → Sign-off
│  │  └─ Normal Return Process: Return Application → Approval → Return Receipt → Inventory Restoration → Refund
│  ├─ 2. Special Test for Inventory Synchronization Consistency (Mandatory)
│  │  ├─ Inventory Reservation: Reservation Success, Reservation Failure
│  │  ├─ Inventory Deduction: Deduction Success, Deduction Failure
│  │  ├─ Order Cancellation & Inventory Release: Release inventory after cancellation, auto release on timeout
│  │  ├─ Message Idempotency: No duplicate operations for repeated inventory messages
│  │  └─ Out-of-order Messages: Normal status transition with disordered deduction/release messages
│  ├─ 3. Boundary Scenario Testing
│  │  ├─ Order validation for zero-stock products
│  │  ├─ High-concurrency Flash Sale (Prevent overselling & under-selling)
│  │  ├─ Partial Shipment / Split Shipment
│  │  └─ Return Scenario & Inventory Restoration Validation
│  ├─ 4. Core API Validation
│  │  ├─ Order Creation API: Parameter check, required fields, error codes
│  │  ├─ Inventory Operation API: Pre-lock / Deduction / Release, response code validation
│  │  ├─ Payment Callback API: Signature verification, idempotency, status write-back
│  │  └─ WMS Callback API: Shipment & sign-off callback, field validation
│  └─ 5. Exception Handling & Compensation Strategy (Mandatory)
│     ├─ API / Message Timeout Handling
│     ├─ API Retry Mechanism (Payment, WMS, Inventory)
│     ├─ Service Circuit Breaker & Degradation Strategy
│     ├─ Scheduled Compensation Tasks (Stuck orders, inventory discrepancy, message resending)
│     └─ Data Rollback & Status Recovery after Failures
├─ Q Quality
│  ├─ 1. Performance Metrics
│  │  ├─ Concurrent TPS: Metrics for order, payment and inventory APIs
│  │  ├─ Response Latency: P95 response time standard
│  │  ├─ System Error Rate Threshold
│  │  └─ Message Queue Throughput & Backlog Control
│  ├─ 2. Reliability
│  │  ├─ Validation for Timeout, Retry, Circuit Breaker & Degradation
│  │  ├─ Fault Tolerance for External Dependencies (WMS / SC2P)
│  │  ├─ No service interruption when single cluster node fails
│  │  └─ No message loss or duplicate consumption
│  ├─ 3. Observability
│  │  ├─ Full-link Logging (Order, Inventory, Callback)
│  │  ├─ Core Monitoring Metrics: Inventory discrepancy rate, message backlog, stuck orders
│  │  └─ Alert Rules: Inventory anomaly, message backlog, stuck order alert
│  ├─ 4. Security Capability
│  │  ├─ API Authentication & Access Permission Control
│  │  ├─ Sensitive Data Masking (Phone number, address, payment information)
│  │  └─ Anti-brush & Malicious Request Interception
│  └─ 5. Recoverability
│     ├─ Fault Drills: Database, MQ and third-party service failure drills
│     ├─ Abnormal Data Repair Process (Dirty data of inventory & orders)
│     └─ Data Backup & Version Rollback Validation
├─ Release Entry & Exit Criteria (Mandatory)
│  ├─ Entry Criteria (Test Start Conditions)
│  │  ├─ All smoke test cases of main flow passed
│  │  ├─ Test environment & WMS/SC2P joint debugging environment ready
│  │  ├─ Data isolation completed
│  │  └─ Monitoring & alerts configured and effective
│  └─ Exit Criteria (Release to Production)
│     ├─ 100% of core functional test cases passed
│     ├─ All inventory synchronization scenarios passed; no overselling or data inconsistency
│     ├─ All performance metrics met requirements; no performance bottlenecks
│     ├─ No P0/P1 defects; P2 defect repair rate meets standard
│     └─ Reconciliation & compensation mechanisms verified
└─ Test Strategy Note
   ├─ Priority Classification
   │  ├─ P0 Highest Priority: Inventory consistency, order state machine, idempotency control
   │  ├─ P1 Second Priority: Main business flow, exception compensation, concurrency & performance
   │  ├─ P2 Medium Priority: Boundary scenarios, security, monitoring & alerting
   │  └─ P3 Low Priority: Edge interactions, minor prompt optimization
   └─ Risks & Trade-offs
      ├─ Inventory Risk: Cover risks via reconciliation & scheduled compensation; real-time monitoring and alerts
      ├─ Concurrency Risk: Optimize via pressure test; adopt traffic limiting & degradation to guarantee core flow
      └─ External Dependency Risk: Isolate faults via circuit breaker to avoid system avalanche


电商系统MFQ测试计划
├─ M Models 模型层
│  ├─ 1.端到端订单业务流模型
│  │  ├─ 正常主流程：浏览商品→加购→下单→支付→库存扣减→WMS发货→签收→订单完成
│  │  └─ 异常分支：支付失败/订单取消/部分发货/退货退款/超卖场景
│  ├─ 2.订单状态机模型
│  │  ├─ 订单状态：待支付、已支付、待发货、已发货、已签收、已完成、已关闭、已退款
│  │  ├─ 合法状态流转规则
│  │  ├─ 非法状态跳转拦截校验
│  │  └─ 超时自动流转（待支付超时自动关单）
│  ├─ 3.库存状态模型
│  │  ├─ 库存状态：可售、预锁定、已扣减、已释放、退货回补
│  │  ├─ 下单：商品库存预锁定
│  │  ├─ 支付成功：预锁定转为正式扣减
│  │  ├─ 取消/支付超时：预锁定库存释放
│  │  └─ 退货/拒收：商品库存回补恢复可售
│  ├─ 4.外部系统交互模型
│  │  ├─ 前端商城 ↔ WMS仓储系统：出库单、发货通知、签收通知
│  │  ├─ 前端商城 ↔ SC2P支付系统：支付回调、退款回调
│  │  ├─ 同步方式：同步调用、异步消息、回调通知
│  │  └─ 基础机制：请求重试、消息幂等、异常兜底
│  └─ 5.数据一致性边界模型
│     ├─ 强一致性范围：库存实时扣减、订单支付状态
│     ├─ 最终一致性范围：WMS发货状态、跨系统库存对账
│     └─ 对账节点：T+1库存对账、订单状态对账、消息日志对账
├─ F Functional 功能层
│  ├─ 1.核心主干流程（正常路径）
│  │  ├─ 完整下单+支付+发货+签收流程
│  │  └─ 正常申请退货→审核→退货入库→库存回补→退款
│  ├─ 2.库存同步一致性专项（强制项）
│  │  ├─ 库存预留场景：预留成功、预留失败
│  │  ├─ 库存扣减场景：扣减成功、扣减失败
│  │  ├─ 订单取消&库存释放：取消订单释放库存、超时自动释放
│  │  ├─ 消息幂等：重复下发库存消息，不重复执行操作
│  │  └─ 消息乱序：扣减/释放消息顺序颠倒，状态正常流转
│  ├─ 3.边界场景测试
│  │  ├─ 零库存商品下单校验
│  │  ├─ 高并发秒杀（防超卖、防少卖）
│  │  ├─ 部分发货/拆分发货场景
│  │  └─ 退货场景&库存回补校验
│  ├─ 4.核心API校验
│  │  ├─ 订单创建API：入参校验、必填项、错误码
│  │  ├─ 库存操作API：预扣/扣减/释放、返回码校验
│  │  ├─ 支付回调API：签名、幂等、状态回写
│  │  └─ WMS回调API：发货/签收回调、字段校验
│  └─ 5.异常处理&补偿策略（强制项）
│     ├─ 接口/消息超时处理
│     ├─ 接口重试机制（支付、WMS、库存）
│     ├─ 服务熔断&降级策略
│     ├─ 定时补偿任务（死单、库存差异、消息补发）
│     └─ 故障后数据回滚与状态修复
├─ Q Quality 质量层
│  ├─ 1.性能指标
│  │  ├─ 并发TPS：订单、支付、库存接口指标
│  │  ├─ 响应延迟：P95响应耗时标准
│  │  ├─ 系统错误率阈值
│  │  └─ 消息队列吞吐量&堆积控制
│  ├─ 2.可靠性
│  │  ├─ 超时、重试、熔断、降级验证
│  │  ├─ 外部依赖（WMS/SC2P）故障容错
│  │  ├─ 集群单节点故障无业务中断
│  │  └─ 消息不丢失、不重复消费
│  ├─ 3.可观测性
│  │  ├─ 全链路日志（订单、库存、回调）
│  │  ├─ 核心监控指标：库存差异率、消息积压、死单量
│  │  └─ 告警规则：库存异常、消息堆积、订单卡死告警
│  ├─ 4.安全能力
│  │  ├─ 接口鉴权、访问权限控制
│  │  ├─ 敏感数据脱敏（手机号、地址、支付信息）
│  │  └─ 防刷、恶意请求拦截
│  └─ 5.可恢复性
│     ├─ 故障演练：数据库、MQ、第三方服务故障演练
│     ├─ 异常数据修复流程（库存/订单脏数据）
│     └─ 数据备份、版本回滚验证
├─ 发布准入/准出标准（强制项）
│  ├─ 准入标准（测试启动条件）
│  │  ├─ 主干流程冒烟用例全部通过
│  │  ├─ 测试环境&WMS/SC2P联调环境就绪
│  │  ├─ 数据隔离完成
│  │  └─ 监控、告警配置生效
│  └─ 准出标准（上线发布条件）
│     ├─ 核心功能用例100%通过
│     ├─ 库存同步场景全部通过，无超卖/数据不一致
│     ├─ 性能指标达标，无性能瓶颈
│     ├─ 无P0/P1缺陷，P2缺陷修复率达标
│     └─ 对账、补偿机制验证通过
└─ 测试策略说明
   ├─ 优先级划分
   │  ├─ P0最高优先级：库存一致性、订单状态机、幂等控制
   │  ├─ P1次优先级：主流程、异常补偿、并发性能
   │  ├─ P2中优先级：边界场景、安全、监控告警
   │  └─ P3低优先级：边缘交互、次要提示优化
   └─ 风险与取舍
      ├─ 库存风险：对账+定时补偿兜底，实时监控告警
      ├─ 并发风险：压测优化+限流降级保障核心流程
      └─ 外部依赖风险：熔断隔离，避免服务雪崩
